Class LogFactory<T extends LogFactory.Entry,O extends Indexed>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.DataObjectFactory<BDO>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of log Entry
    O - Type of owning object
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contexed, ContextCached, FormCreatorProducer, FormUpdateProducer<T>, FilterMatcher<T>, TableStructureTransitionTarget, TableTransitionTarget, TypeConverter<T,java.lang.Number>, Selector<DataObjectItemInput<T>>, Owner, IndexedProducer<T>, Tagged, Targetted<T>

    public abstract class LogFactory<T extends LogFactory.Entry,O extends Indexed>
extends TableStructureDataObjectFactory<T>
    general log Entry class. Consists of a series of date-stamped entries of mutable class. Each entry has an operator who added the entry and a integer tag that references an object that implements Indexed and an Owning object
    Author:
    spb

      • makeBDO

        protected final DataObject makeBDO(Repository.Record res)
                            throws DataFault
        Description copied from class: DataObjectFactory
        Construct a new Blank DataObject of the correct Class This method takes a Record as an argument. This allows the factory to either create different sub-classes depending on a value in the record or to produce objects from different Repositories/tables. We keep the return type as DataObject instead of making it generic as this helps with legacy compatibility a little bit (problem is if we have another generic sub-type between us and a legacy sub-class
        Specified by:
